abstract: Popularity of Donald Trump's political campaign has dominated news and polls but question of whether he can translate that popularity into victories in early contest states remains; Trump appears to have lagged behind other candidates in setting up ground game in Iowa before its first-in-the-nation caucuses, which bodes ill for his performance both in those caucuses and in subsequent primaries.
lead_paragraph: Despite continued strength in polls, organizers have fallen behind some of their own benchmarks with six weeks to go, possibly imperiling chances of victories in early nominating states.

headline.main: Donald Trump Campaign Lags in Mobilizing Iowa Caucus Voters
headline.print_headline: Strong in Polls, Yet Trump Lags on the Ground
